Anniversary of Kim Il Sung's work observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 1 (KCNA) - Papers here Thursday observe the 11th anniversary of President Kim Il Sung's famous work "Let Us Achieve the Great Unity of Our Nation" (August 1, 1991).
 The articles say the work makes a systematic and comprehensive compilation of ideas and theories on great national unity on the basis of the immortal Juche idea and gives clear-cut solutions to theoretical and practical issues concerning national unity.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the essence of the work that national harmony and unity precisely means national reunification.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Referring to the tasks for great national unity and ways for their implementation, the work says all the Koreans in the north, south and abroad should put the common interests of the nation above anything else, devote everything to the cause of national reunification, invigorate contacts and travels and further develop dialogue among them, transcending differences in ideology, social system and religious belief.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun says:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His idea of great national unity and his cause of national reunification have successfully been carried forward thanks to Kim Jong Il's outstanding leadership.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean nation should implement the June 15 inter-Korean joint declaration to the letter and accelerate the independent reunification of the country under the motto of "concerted efforts of the Korean nation."&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson says that the cause of national reunification will surely be accomplished on the basis of Kim Il Sung's idea of great national unity and under the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il.

New clone cell breeds produced 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 1 (KCNA) - Researchers of tissue cultivation at Pyongyang University of Medicine recently succeeded in producing clone cell breeds of good biological nature and sensitive to virus.
 The cell breeds can be used for manufacturing medicines to prevent virus-affected diseases and Koryo medicines, for diagnosis and treatment and detecting poison in biological medicines of various kinds.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The production is of importance in developing virology, genetic medical science and cell engineering.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Scores of medical units across the country have successfully introduced to their researches the cells which had been bred after obtaining from the cells of skin, lung, kidney, thymus gland and bone marrow.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These clone cell breeds were produced on the basis of indigenous technology.

Aquarium reconstructed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 1 (KCNA) - The Aquarium of the Central Zoo at the foot of Mt. Taesong in Pyongyang has been reconstructed.
 The aquarium covering 1,200 square meters is packed with large and small fish tanks of various shapes, the biggest one being ten cubic meters.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Living in the tanks are a hundred and scores of species of fish and tortoises such as sturgeon, flatfish, amphipion clakkii, trout, colossoma nigrippinnis, clarias sp and megalobrama amblicephala, natives of different oceans and continents.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The visitors can see fur seals and phocidae catching fish.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Sounds of wave and sea gull by sound facilities are available at the aquarium.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The aquarium draws many visitors who are interested in fish and sea animals.

Korean women's national costume 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 1 (KCNA) - Chima (skirt) and jogori (jacket) are one of the peculiar national costumes for the Korean women.
 This thousands of years old way of dressing has undergone changes and improvement to suit the taste, carriage and life style of the Korean women who like mild climate and clean and bright things. The main style of present-day chima and jogori dates back to the middle period of Koguryo, Paekje and Silla kingdoms.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There are two kinds of chima: kkorichima and tongchima.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The first is wide and long.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Material for chima and its color vary according to the season and are richly patterned.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Jogori is cut small and short so as to fit tightly.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean women like to wear elegant and gorgeous chima and jogori at wedding ceremonies, on holidays and other days.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
 Korean clothes shops and garment factories across the country are further developing the style and decorations of chima and jogori to meet the contemporary aesthetic taste.

U.S. aerial espionage, war exercises against DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 1 (KCNA) - The U.S. imperialists made more than 180 espionage flights against the DPRK in July with various types of strategic and tactical reconnaissance planes including U-2 and RC-135, according to military sources.
 Between July 24 and 26 they also staged manoeuvres, dubbed "theory," for estimating combat preparations against the DPRK, with the mobilization of hundreds of fighter bombers and assault planes.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nearly 2,000 fighter planes were involved in aerial war exercises in July.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The aerial espionage and military exercises were aimed to complete preparations of combat actions of flying corps according to the operational plan for aggression on the DPRK.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 That is an indication that the U.S. imperialists are seeking a surprise preemptive strike at the DPRK.

Chinese military attache hosts reception 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 1 (KCNA) - Chinese military attache Yan Jiangfeng hosted a reception at his embassy last evening on the occasion of the 75th anniversary of the Chinese People's Liberation Army (CPLA).
 At the reception he said that the heroic Korean People's Army founded and led by President Kim Il Sung has performed immortal feats in defending the country.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He referred to the major role played by the KPA for the increase of the defense capacity of the country, the completion of major projects and economic growth, true to supreme commander Kim Jong Il's policy of giving priority to the army.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The peoples and the armies of the two countries have fought shoulder to shoulder to win great victories and contribute to global peace and the progress of humankind, he said.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Il Chol, minister of the People's Armed Forces, in his reply extended the warmest congratulations and militant salute to the officers and men of the CPLA on behalf of the KPA servicemen on the occasion.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Since its foundation the CPLA has honorably discharged its noble mission and duty before the party, the country and the people and made great contributions to liberating the whole country, building a genuine people's state where the working people have become masters of the state, defending the country and stepping up socialist construction, he said.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He sincerely wished the officers and men of the CPLA greater success in their struggle to ensure the absolute leadership of the party over the army, increase the combat capacity of its units and accelerate the unification of the country.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saying that the DPRK-China friendship is being carried forward and developed generation after generation, he said that the Korean army and people will as ever exert positive efforts to boost the friendship true to the intention of Kim Jong Il.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reception was also attended by KPA lt. General Ji Yong Chun, other generals and officers, officials concerned, diplomatic envoys and military attaches of different countries here.

Proper stand on inter-Korean relations called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 1 (KCNA) - If the inter-Korean authorities-to-authorities dialogue is to prove fruitful to meet the nation's aspiration and expectation, it is important to make a correct review of the inter-Korean relations which have undergone ups and downs and draw a lesson from it. 
 Rodong Sinmun today says this in a signed commentary.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The results of the review teach a precious and serious lesson that the north and the south should remain true to "by our nation itself," the spirit of the June 15 joint declaration, and abandon the old hostile viewpoint of confrontation.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is another lesson that as long as the anti-reunification forces keen to live in reliance on foreign forces are allowed to stay, it is impossible to implement the joint declaration and furthermore, the nation may be exterminated.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south side has never properly uttered the words "by our nation itself" since the north-south joint declaration was published.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
 It has consistently maintained the stand of putting greater emphasis on "cooperation" with foreign forces.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There had been multi-faceted dialogue, contacts, cooperation and exchange between the north and the south since the publication of the June 15 joint declaration, but the reconciliation and unity of the nation have not been achieved.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
This is chiefly attributable to the south side's insincere attitude and antagonism towards the fellow countrymen in the north.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Anyone with national conscience, though he or she was a right-wing element or conservative yesterday, should respond to the call of the era and the nation and make a bold decision to break with outside forces and join hands with the fellow countrymen.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The north will cooperate with anyone willing to achieve reconciliation and unity of the nation and the reunification of the country through its concerted efforts as a member of an independent party to the dialogue free from outside interference and pressure and away from the conception of the cold war confrontation, implement the joint declaration to the letter and Certainly keep the promise made to the nation.
